The paper deals with the use of multi-antenna arrays in wireless communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the characterization of the ergodic average of the mutual information for realistic correlated channels, which is related to the Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of mathematical methods that are valid for large antenna numbers, which is related to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the calculation of the outage capacity, which is related to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
